    "Therapists must adapt to every situation if they want to treat patients successfully.",
    "This characterizes psychotherapy and distinguishes it from experimental psychology.",
    "In psychotherapy, there are many ways to work with patients/clients which are no better or worse than other methods, but one may be more suitable for the individual psychotherapist and patient-therapist constellation.",
